John Panzer wrote:

&gt;
&gt; We may be talking past each other; what would you expect if you
&gt; applied DELETE to the collection URI rather than GET?
&gt; 

I wouldn&#39;t expect anything.  Atom Protocol leaves the deletion of
collections undefined, which means it could go either way.  Since
members can belong to multiple collections, it seems wiser to me, to
not delete individual members when a collection is deleted.  Unless my
application logic constrains resources to only be members of one
collection.

-Eric
